{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Psa|52","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","chapter":52,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v11","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:52:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":52,"verse":1,"text":"Why boast about evil, you hero! God’s faithful love is constant.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:52:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":52,"verse":2,"text":"Like a sharpened razor, your tongue devises destruction, working treachery.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:52:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":52,"verse":3,"text":"You love evil instead of good, lying instead of speaking truthfully. Selah","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:52:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":52,"verse":4,"text":"You love any words that destroy, you treacherous tongue!","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:52:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":52,"verse":5,"text":"This is why God will bring you down forever. He will take you, ripping you out of your tent; he will uproot you from the land of the living. Selah","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:52:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":52,"verse":6,"text":"The righteous will see and fear, and they will derisively say about that hero,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:52:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":52,"verse":7,"text":"“Here is the man who would not make God his refuge, but trusted in the abundance of his riches, taking refuge in his destructive behavior.”","textR